title: multicellular organism
definition: Anatomical structure that is an individual member of a species and consists of more than one cell.

nodes.title: head
nodes.definition: The head is the anterior-most division of the body [GO].

nodes.title: left antenna
nodes.definition: The appendage that is composed of ringlike sclerites and the anatomical structures encircled by these sclerites and that is articulated with the cranium.

nodes.title: right antenna
nodes.definition: The appendage that is composed of ringlike sclerites and the anatomical structures encircled by these sclerites and that is articulated with the cranium.

nodes.title: thorax
nodes.definition: The tagma that is composed of the prothorax, mesothorax and metathorax.

nodes.title: abdomen
nodes.definition: The tagma that is located posterior to the thorax.
